RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FRENCHIES GOLD took the lead at the thirteen sixteenths pole and angled to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure toward the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on well. SPARKLEINYOUREYE rated close inside on the opening turn, started a three wide bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and had to settle for second. JACKYSINTHECASTLE saved ground off the pace, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, flattened in the lane and just lasted for third. CLOUD MOVER saved ground well off the pace on the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and just missed third in an even finish. SNEAKY LYNK stalked from the three path the first turn, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded past the five sixteenths. LOCKDOWN VANNA stalked the pace in the three and four paths the first turn, left the turn outside and faded past the seven sixteenths pole. TIMES CHANGED UPON REVIEW.

ENTRY.NAME: Sparkleinyoureye
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,3wd bid 7/16,off rail far turn,settled 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Frenchies Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured near 3/8,rail far turn,held well drvg

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 21800. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAG HARBOR settled inside on the first turn, started a bid nearing the seven sixteenths pole and improved at the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady encouragement leaving the turn, got up in the final yards and raced clear toward the wire. BAAGY settled off the rail on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and took the lead at the rail at the five sixteenths pole, raced clear approaching the quarter pole, widened through the far turn but was caught flattening stride late. SPRITZER set the early pace inside, was caught leaving the first turn and dueled from that point, but faded into the far turn. BOWIE TWO STEP stalked the pace from the three path the first turn, took the lead into the backstretch and dueled from that point, was caught at the five sixteenths pole and flattened in the three path of the far turn. PRINCE OF FENTON stalked the early pace two deep but dropped back from between horses leaving the half mile pole and faded through the backstretch. DIVINING DANCER was taken up on the first turn and walked off post race.

ENTRY.NAME: Sag Harbor
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace inside,bid 7/16,rail far turn,up late,cleared

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: URBAN BANDIT settled in the three path the first turn, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole and improved at the rail on the far turn, eased out to take aim at COLLECTORATE nearing the head of the lane, dug in leaving the turn, lugged in and made light contact with that one and took the nod in the final strides. The latter rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole and dueled clear toward the quarter, rounded the far turn at the rail, dug in under steady stretch handling but was brushed late and missed the nod. ELFUEGOMASBRILANTE saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole and raced near the rail on the far turn, then dueled through the stretch for third. ARROGANT RIDER settled off the early pace about the four path and left the first turn outside, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn then relented in the stretch duel for third. MR MAJESTIC stalked three wide on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded through the far turn. MALIBU ROCK STAR hesitated leaving the gate, saved ground on the opening turn and showed little response through the backstretch. BUY HERE PAY HERE stalked two deep then challenged approaching the three eighths pole, but dropped back toward the quarter and weakened leaving the far turn. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed, a claim of foul against the rider of Urban Bandit for interference in late stretch, lodged by the rider of Collectorate.

ENTRY.NAME: Urban Bandit
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace 3p,bid 3/8,aim off rail 1/8,lug in,brushed late,nod wire

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDERINREADYRICK took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and angled to the inside to rate the pace, was kept in hand through the backstretch, mildly pressured into the far turn then taken in hand the final sixteenth. WELL EQUIPPED settled in the three and four paths on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn then dueled through the stretch for second. THEWITCHISGONE settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail but drifted leaving the turn and relented in the stretch duel for second. SPIRIT OF WINDSOR raced two deep on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and showed little further. LEG UP rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase from the three eighths pole, came through the far turn in the four path and showed little in the lane. CHASE LIL ME showed little response. SPECTACULO settled off the rail on the first turn and was through after a half mile.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 79. Allowance Purse 35100. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL PAIN rated a slim lead inside, was met and dueled ICING past the half mile pole, contested the rail and recovered the nod midway on the far turn, cleared that one leaving the eighth pole and held well with steady encouragement. The latter tapered in and stalked two deep on the first turn, challenged and dueled with the edge past the half mile pole, contested the far turn two deep, gave up the nod midway through the turn then relented in the duel through the stretch. PERSONABLE saved ground on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening stride. JAXJAXXORJACKS raced in the six path the first turn and left the turn outside, gave chase past the half mile pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and ran evenly in the lane. NOCASHREFUNDS rounded the first turn about the four path, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn then flattened in the lane. JUBA BOUND saved ground on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the three and four paths of the far turn. MODERN DAY ROMANCE rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole but showed little response. REATA'S CASTLE rounded the first turn in the five path then faded through the backstretch. TIMES CHANGED UPON REVIEW.

ENTRY.NAME: Royal Pain
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead,met 1/2,dueled,nod mid turn,cleared,held well

TIMETOGETUP rated just off the pace inside on the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn, dueled through the stretch for second and just held on. PEARLY GHOST rated close inside the first turn, picked up the chase from the half mile pole, rounded the far turn off the rail, eased out into the lane and finished well while gaining on the runner-up. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 15700. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 8, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND FIBER chased inside, raced close at the rail on the turn, took the lead approaching the head of the lane and ran clear leaving the turn, dug in under steady handling and held on. FREEDOM IS RINGING chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, dueled for second toward mid-stretch and was gaining on the winner. FU MAN SUE was hustled through the opening quarter and drew to even terms at the five sixteenths pole, contested the turn off the rail, bore out approaching the head of the lane but came back to claim third. GRUMPELSTILTSKIN chased toward mid track, rounded the turn about the six path, left the turn outside and improved his position. SHACKLEFORDS STORM set a pressured pace the opening quarter mile, was met at the five sixteenths pole and contested even terms off the rail on the turn, but dropped back leaving the turn and weakened. ROSE'S GALAXY gave chase toward the outside, rounded the turn about the three path and showed little more. SHACKLED chased through the backstretch, raced in the five path of the turn and showed little in the lane. DOESN'T MAKE CENTS gave chase outside and raced in the six path of the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Grand Fiber
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,close rail turn,up near 1/8,cleared,held on driving
